[2026-03-18T11:48:07.810Z] [STDOUT] {"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01M4u4Nm1zhzL1Giu3VXeiqj","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01TXgt3QRAJCvCSHPUqgf61Y","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"SCAN_ID=\"5f014f2a-1ad2-4f4f-8152-28198e0297c3\"\n\n# Idea 1: Predictive Cost Anomaly Engine\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"scan_id\": \"'$SCAN_ID'\",\n    \"project_id\": \"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\",\n    \"context_id\": \"ctx_1773782663367_bj2fyhb\",\n    \"scan_type\": \"moonshot_architect\",\n    \"category\": \"functionality\",\n    \"title\": \"Predictive Cost Anomaly Engine with Auto-Budgets\",\n    \"description\": \"Transform the daily_metrics aggregation from a passive summary into a predictive anomaly detection engine. Instead of just recording cost_usd and duration_ms totals, build time-series forecasting directly into the retention pipeline. When aggregating daily metrics, compute rolling statistical baselines (mean, stddev, trend) per persona and auto-detect cost spikes, duration regressions, or failure rate surges before they become billing surprises. First sprint: add rolling_avg_cost and rolling_stddev columns to daily_metrics and compute them during the existing retention aggregation step.\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"The current system collects rich execution data (cost, duration, tokens, status) but only stores flat daily sums—all the predictive signal is destroyed during purge. With per-tenant SQLite already isolating data, adding lightweight statistical columns is architecturally cheap. This would make personas-cloud the only AI orchestration platform that proactively warns you before cost overruns happen, not after.\",\n    \"effort\": 7,\n    \"impact\": 9,\n    \"risk\": 5\n  }'\n\necho \"\"\necho \"---\"\n\n# Idea 2: Federated Metrics Fabric\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"scan_id\": \"'$SCAN_ID'\",\n    \"project_id\": \"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\",\n    \"context_id\": \"ctx_1773782663367_bj2fyhb\",\n    \"scan_type\": \"moonshot_architect\",\n    \"category\": \"functionality\",\n    \"title\": \"Federated Cross-Tenant Metrics Fabric\",\n    \"description\": \"Build a federated analytics layer that can query daily_metrics across all tenant databases without centralizing data. Currently runRetention iterates tenants sequentially and metrics stay siloed per-tenant. Create an in-memory virtual table or query router that exposes aggregate views (total platform cost, busiest personas, failure hotspots) by querying each tenant DB on-demand and merging results. This preserves tenant isolation while enabling platform-wide observability. First sprint: add a /api/metrics/platform endpoint that iterates tenantDbManager.listTenantIds() and aggregates daily_metrics across tenants into a unified response.\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"The multi-tenant architecture with per-tenant SQLite files is elegant for isolation but creates a blind spot: there is no platform-level view of system health or usage. Operators cannot answer basic questions like total daily cost or which persona has the highest failure rate across all tenants. A federated query approach avoids data centralization while unlocking platform-level intelligence—this is the architectural pattern that makes personas-cloud viable as a managed service.\",\n    \"effort\": 8,\n    \"impact\": 9,\n    \"risk\": 6\n  }'\n\necho \"\"\necho \"---\"\n\n# Idea 3: Intelligent Adaptive Retention\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"scan_id\": \"'$SCAN_ID'\",\n    \"project_id\": \"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\",\n    \"context_id\": \"ctx_1773782663367_bj2fyhb\",\n    \"scan_type\": \"moonshot_architect\",\n    \"category\": \"user_benefit\",\n    \"title\": \"Self-Tuning Retention with Value-Aware Purging\",\n    \"description\": \"Replace the fixed retentionDays config with an intelligent retention engine that keeps high-value executions longer and purges low-value ones sooner. Use the execution metadata already available (cost_usd, status, duration_ms, retry_count) to compute a value score per execution. Failed executions with error_message containing novel error patterns are preserved for debugging; repetitive successful runs of the same persona are purged aggressively. The TABLE_REGISTRY maxPurgeFraction already provides safety rails. First sprint: add a value_score computed column to the _ret_ids temp table collection step and sort purge candidates by ascending value score.\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"Fixed retention windows are a blunt instrument—they treat a one-cent test run and a fifty-dollar multi-hour execution identically. The retention pipeline already touches every row via the batched index scan, so computing a value heuristic adds minimal overhead. This would be a genuinely novel capability: no AI orchestration platform offers value-aware data lifecycle management. It turns retention from a cost center into a strategic advantage.\",\n    \"effort\": 6,\n    \"impact\": 8,\n    \"risk\": 5\n  }'\n\necho \"\"\necho \"---\"\n\n# Idea 4: Real-Time Metrics Stream\ncurl -s -X POST http://localhost:3000/api/ideas \\\n  -H \"Content-Type: application/json\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"scan_id\": \"'$SCAN_ID'\",\n    \"project_id\": \"c6fd0474-19f1-4223-b6a9-752077c51d3d\",\n    \"context_id\": \"ctx_1773782663367_bj2fyhb\",\n    \"scan_type\": \"moonshot_architect\",\n    \"category\": \"functionality\",\n    \"title\": \"Live Execution Metrics via Kafka Event Stream\",\n    \"description\": \"Eliminate the 24-hour metrics blind spot by publishing execution completion events to Kafka in real-time, enabling live dashboards and instant alerting. Currently metrics only materialize during the daily retention aggregation—meaning a cost spike at 9 AM is not visible until the next day. Emit a lightweight metrics event on every execution status change through the existing Kafka infrastructure (kafkaEnabled is already configured). Build a complementary real-time_metrics table that accumulates minute-level granularity alongside the daily rollup. First sprint: add a Kafka producer call in updateExecution (executions.ts) when status transitions to completed/failed, publishing persona_id, cost_usd, duration_ms, and status.\",\n    \"reasoning\": \"The Kafka infrastructure already exists in the codebase but is used only for event dispatching. The daily retention aggregation creates a massive observability gap where operators are flying blind for up to 24 hours. Real-time metrics streaming transforms personas-cloud from a batch-analytics system into a live operations platform. Combined with the existing per-tenant isolation, this creates the foundation for SLA monitoring, auto-scaling triggers, and real-time cost controls that would define the product category.\",\n    \"effort\": 7,\n    \"impact\": 10,\n    \"risk\": 6\n  }'","description":"Save all 4 moonshot ideas to Vibeman API"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":419,"cache_read_input_tokens":40768,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":419},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"4e9e3da1-5432-4afe-a747-00b21742131c","uuid":"a6b3684d-e28c-4c78-9dd1-d9ea2d8e334b"}
